<div id="review_25489019" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/25489019" />
    <a title="Petra X is enjoying a road trip across the NE USA" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1237196-petra-x-is-enjoying-a-road-trip-across-the-ne-usa"><img alt="Petra X is enjoying a road trip across the NE USA" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603179398p2/1237196.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/25489019?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Petra X is enjoying a road trip across the NE USA" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Petra X is enjoying a road trip across the NE USA" href="/user/show/1237196-petra-x-is-enjoying-a-road-trip-across-the-ne-usa">Petra X is enjoying a road trip across the NE USA</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780751541984" href="/book/show/17996790-midnight-express">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1237196-petra-x-is-enjoying-a-road-trip-across-the-ne-usa?shelf=biography-true-story">biography-true-story</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1237196-petra-x-is-enjoying-a-road-trip-across-the-ne-usa?shelf=travel-adventure-countries">travel-adventure-countries</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1237196-petra-x-is-enjoying-a-road-trip-across-the-ne-usa?shelf=2015-reviews">2015-reviews</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer25489019" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16004084034658095783">I read Midnight Express years ago and I was quite taken by the graphic descriptions of his awful imprisonment and the terrible conditions existing in Turkey at that time for convicts. There are many tv shows, usually about South American or Asian countries prisons which are just as harsh as the ones in this book. It would be interesting to see statistics about the rate of recidivism from prisons with such grim conditions compared with those of the rather hard, tough ones of the US and also with </span>
  <span id="freeText16004084034658095783" style="display:none">I read Midnight Express years ago and I was quite taken by the graphic descriptions of his awful imprisonment and the terrible conditions existing in Turkey at that time for convicts. There are many tv shows, usually about South American or Asian countries prisons which are just as harsh as the ones in this book. It would be interesting to see statistics about the rate of recidivism from prisons with such grim conditions compared with those of the rather hard, tough ones of the US and also with the much easier ones of Europe and especially the Nordic countries. <br /><br />There was a film, screenplay by the wonderful Oliver Stone, which brought the descriptions in the book to life and made the escape much more exciting, as films do. Countries, like people, generally like to show the world only their good side and people certainly sometimes feel shame and humiliation when their unknown, other, darker side is exposed. Turkey certainly felt that the book, and to a much greater extent the film, harmed its international reputation. I wonder if it affected the prison system of the country or they were just careful to have some new, modern, model prisons to show journalists, the UN and other concerned organisations when they come calling?<br /><br /><i>Old review removed at GR's request (!) and replaced with a review written 16 April 2021. The book made a real impression on me as I can remember it in detail despite reading it in the 90s.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="16004084034658095783" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


