<span id="freeTextContainer4378049495665344385">I bought this book because of it’s 4.01 rating on Goodreads. This rates it above similar well-known true stories that were later adapted for films (such as Into the Wild) and even near the heights of extremely well-regarded fictional books like One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s nest.<br/><br/>4.01 stars average?! Are you kidding me? What other books have these other reviewers read such that they would judge THIS one to be among the best of them...? <br/><br/>This book is a terrible read. Yes, it’s nice true story of how a</span>
  <span id="freeText4378049495665344385" style="display:none">I bought this book because of it’s 4.01 rating on Goodreads. This rates it above similar well-known true stories that were later adapted for films (such as Into the Wild) and even near the heights of extremely well-regarded fictional books like One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s nest.<br /><br />4.01 stars average?! Are you kidding me? What other books have these other reviewers read such that they would judge THIS one to be among the best of them...? <br /><br />This book is a terrible read. Yes, it’s nice true story of how a young man escapes from prison mid-way through an unfairly long sentence. But it’s a nice true story written like a high-school English project, and I wouldn’t give a 17-year-old more than a B for this. <br /><br />If you’re reading this whilst deciding whether or not to buy this book, my advice is save yourself the money, but more importantly save yourself the tedium of reading it.<br /><br />Oh and the distance between Imrali Island and the Turkish mainland - which Billy is very keen to tell us is 20 miles (on several occasions) - is actually 8 miles!!</span>
