<span id="freeTextContainer17877515967729554030">Smuggling drugs in or out of Turkey is probably not a great idea. A young William Hayes did not think about that, the downside was years in a Turkish prison the upside is this book. A cracking story from the moment the tale of this young unfortunate American who finds himself with a couple kilos of hashish and no place to go. &apos;Midnight Express&apos; (1977) is a classic memoir of Hayes&apos; time in a Turkish prison, during which he was beaten, had a mental breakdown, and saw his sentence increased from fo</span>
  <span id="freeText17877515967729554030" style="display:none">Smuggling drugs in or out of Turkey is probably not a great idea. A young William Hayes did not think about that, the downside was years in a Turkish prison the upside is this book. A cracking story from the moment the tale of this young unfortunate American who finds himself with a couple kilos of hashish and no place to go. 'Midnight Express' (1977) is a classic memoir of Hayes' time in a Turkish prison, during which he was beaten, had a mental breakdown, and saw his sentence increased from four years to life just as his original term was nearing its end. After five years, he made a dash for freedom – and, as it happened, a fair degree of fame. Following publication shortly after the book was turned into a Oliver Stone film, so William Hayes (according to him), "telling the same bullshit story" for 40 years. That said, a good read. </span>
